Write a program to calculate the stock span for each day.

The stock span for a particular day is defined as the maximum number of consecutive days (including the current day) for which the stock price was less than or equal to the current day's price.
The span always starts from the current day and counts backward consecutively until a day with a higher price is encountered or the beginning of the data is reached.

#include <stdio.h>
int main(){
	int n,i,j;
	scanf("%d",&n);
	int a[n],stock[n];
	for(i=0;i<n;i++){
		scanf("%d",&stock[i]);
	}
	for(i=0;i<n;i++){
		int count=1;
		for(j=i-1;j>=0;j--){
			if(stock[j]<=stock[i]){
				count++;
			}else{
				break;
			}
		}
		a[i]=count;
	}
	for(i=0;i<n;i++){
		printf("%d ",a[i]);
	}
}
